title: Eagles soar over Vikings at Jantz Stadium
text: Previous Next Eagles soar over Vikings at Jantz Stadium ABOVE: Offensive coordinator Lelin George sports his new Viking jacket as he called plays on the sideline Friday. (Olivia Haselwood/Courier) Eagles soar over Vikings at Jantz Stadium Traiton Suttles (1) middle, covers up a fumble to get the Vikings the ball. (Olivia Haselwood/Courier) Eagles soar over Vikings at Jantz Stadium Layke Hoffman (10), back, makes a catch for the only Viking touchdown Friday against Silver Lake. (Olivia Haselwood/Courier) Eagles soar over Vikings at Jantz Stadium Jayden Tate (32) finds a hole to help move the chains Friday against Silver Lake. (Olivia Haselwood/Courier) Posted: Friday, October 2, 2015 10:58 pm Eagles soar over Vikings at Jantz Stadium By OLIVIA HASELWOOD Courier Sports Reporter sports@winfieldcourier.com   They may have been smaller, but speed and an effective passing game by the Silver Lake Eagles Friday kept the Winfield Vikings in check, defeating them 41–7. The Vikings improved from their 56-0 shutout last year at Silver Lake, but they grappled with a new Eagle play set and missed several opportunities to advance their score at Jantz Stadium. “There is no quit in these guys, and they played hard,” Vikings coach Justin Price said of his team. “The turnovers and penalties hurt, and that was the tale of the game. We moved the ball, but we couldn’t finish drives. When you play a quality program like Silver Lake, you can’t have those mistakes.” Silver Lake received the ball to start the game. They drove the ball down the field in just over four minutes to score. The kick was no good to put the Eagles up 6-0. On the next kickoff, the Vikings fumbled the ball and the Eagles recovered it on the Viking 29-yard line. It took the Eagles less than 15 seconds to score for the second time.
